L
|f|
 L = \lim_{x\to\infty} \left( f(x) + \int_{0}^{x} f(t) \, dt \right) 
 f(x) + \int_{0}^{x} f(t) \, dt = \frac{\frac{d}{dx} \left( e^{x} \int_{0}^{x} f(t) \, dt \right) }{\frac{d}{dx} e^{x}}. 
 \lim_{x\to\infty} \int_{0}^{x} f(t) \, dt = \lim_{x\to\infty} \frac{e^{x} \int_{0}^{x} f(t) \, dt}{e^{x}} = L
\lim_{x\to\infty} f(x) = \lim_{x\to\infty} \left( f(x) + \int_{0}^{x} f(t) \, dt - \int_{0}^{x} f(t) \, dt \right) = L - L = 0. 
L = \lim_{x \to \infty} f(x)+\int_0^x f(t)dt
\phi(x) = e^x \int_0^x f(t)dt
\phi
\phi(0) = 0
\lim_{x \to \infty} e^{-x}\phi'(x) = L
\epsilon>0
x_0
x \ge x_0
|e^{-x}\phi'(x)-L| < \epsilon
|\phi'(x)-e^{x}L| < e^x \epsilon
[x_0,x]
| \phi(x)-\phi(x_0)-(e^x-e^{x_0})L| < (e^x-e^{x_0}) \epsilon
e^{-x}
| e^{-x}\phi(x)-e^{-x}\phi(x_0)-(1-e^{x_0-x})L| < (1-e^{x_0-x}) \epsilon
x \to \infty
\limsup_{x \to \infty} | e^{-x}\phi(x) -L| \le \epsilon
